<page>
    <shortlink>api table remove function</shortlink>
   <topic>TABLE_REMOVE Function</topic>
   
    <description>Remove an DBF table and all it's associated files.</description>
    
    
   <prototype>L table_remove(C tablename )</prototype>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>tablename</name>
         <description>The path and filename of a .DBF file.
</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
  
   <discussion>
The TABLE_REMOVE() function removes all the files associated with a Alpha Anywhere table.

   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
table_remove("C:\Databases\mydb\my_database.Dbf")
]]></example>
   <limitations>Desktop applications only.</limitations>
   <see>
        <ref link="Table Object Functions and Methods">Table Object Functions and Methods</ref>
        <ref link="Table Functions">Other Table Functions</ref>
   </see>
<terms>table,filename,function</terms>




</page>